fields.description:
Pending multipart uploads are not cleaned up before deleting the containing bucket. Bucket deletion operation (File.delete) fails as the filesystem directory is not empty. The corresponding bucket entity is deleted from the Walrus database long before and these errors are simply dropped. Part records are untouched in the Walrus database which might be useful for cleaning up the parts.

Filesystem resources taken up by the unfinished multipart uploads are never freed up. In addition to fixing this bug in the next release, also need to come up with a way to clean the orphaned multipart uploads left around from 4.0.0.
